  <div class="features-block">
    <div id="featuresRow" class="features-row">
      <div class="left-part description wow slideInLeft">
        <div class="header">
          Auto-grading code
        </div>
        <div class="text">
          We offer two forms of automated code grading.  Our standard grading is dialog driven and usually covers at least 80% of use cases. It covers argument and stdin inputs and handles multiple test cases for full code coverage. Advanced grading lets you write your own grading scripts in any language you choose. This allows you to use any 3rd party testing or support libraries and analyze any aspects of student code.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="middle-part">
        <div id="row1" class="vertical-dot-line">
          <div class="top"></div>
          <div class="dot"></div>
          <div class="bottom"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="right-part screen wow slideInRight">
        <%= image_tag 'assets/features/grading/std-autograde.jpg', alt: 'Standard autograding', class: 'img-responsive' %>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="features-row">
      <div class="left-part screen wow slideInLeft">
        <%= image_tag 'assets/features/grading/mcq.jpg', alt: 'Other autograding', class: 'img-responsive' %>
      </div>
      <div class="middle-part">
        <div id="row2" class="vertical-dot-line">
          <div class="top"></div>
          <div class="dot"></div>
          <div class="bottom"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="right-part description wow slideInRight">
        <div class="header">
          Other auto-graded assessments
        </div>
